<br>
Bilbo is the essence of lotr,says unrealdwarf    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck is undefeated,and I&#39;ve been playing it for a month on tournaments in Croatia.Now you&#39;re<br>
gonna say &quot;croatia,where is that?,they probably don&#39;t know what is lotr&quot;.There is nothing I can do about that >:-( It is FOTR only.Now,you bid 3,if you start 1. pull Bilbo,if not,you will draw a farmer or Bilbo very soon.The farmer is dumped once he does his job.Bilbo is invincible once he gets the consorting,make him skirmish every turn,and aragorn will heal that exertion on boz.The deck decreases the site number by 3,and Bilbo removes any twilight given in the fellowship.Once bilbo gets a sword,he can be thrown to any minion except the troll and the W-k.<br>
Since one minion per turn is handled for free via Bilbo,there is max. one more to be dealt with (except with moria,later about that).1-5 stealths can do,later on boz and aragorn can fight,merry is a great pump,and you can simply throw some more ally&#39;s.The unique possesions are single for drawing,the horn is double because it is like a center of the strategy.I mostly run 1-3,3-5,5-7,7-9.The 5-7 jump can sometimes be hard,not because of wounds,but if you didn&#39;t pull the talent and strangers.The 2 athelas are used on site 7,when preparing to jump,to heal boz if necessary,and merry so he can add  strenght to Frodo.Tasks:<br>
Frodo-heals Bilbo all the time (or bounder if needed)<br>
Boz-horn,fights,stranger<br>
Merry-adds strenght to win skirmishes or saves Frodo,a talent<br>
Aragorn-heals boz,stranger,bow,fights nazgul on his own,takes wounds<br>
<br>
Taking care of certain problems:<br>
Troll-boz and armor,or 2 ally&#39;s via horn,or double exert boz for +6 on bilbo-via horn,frodo-sword and bounder,frodo and merry-sword on one of them<br>
Balrog-same as troll,xcept bilbo needs a sword<br>
Wk-stealth if earlier,boz and merry,gorn and merry,bilbo and double exert boz,frodo merry/frodo bounder and one sword,preferable to direct shoot him with a. bow once,so that you don&#39;t have to face him again<br>
Swarm-there is plenty of hobbit protection,the least problems are with moria<br>
Uruk hai-they dont get enough twilight,there are 4 companions,worry can be a problem if not removed with bilbo and consorting<br>
Sauron-low twilight,and boz is never overwhelmed,if he is there&#39;s merry<br>
Nazgul-low twilight,stealthing early game when the nazgul player is expected to hit the hardest,brands and merry,aragorns bow for a wound and not having to face the nazgul 2 times,filibert bolger<br>
Isengard orcs-I cant tell you anything about that,since no1 plays a clean orc deck around here<br>
<br>
The shadow is simple moria swarm.-1 warrior,+1 troll.I don&#39;t like the Balrog,neither do I need it.<br>
Don&#39;t forget you can remove conditions with bilbo and consorting! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=26379"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=26379" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
